    "methodology": "Relative poverty is the standard UK measure: households with income below 60% of the contemporary median, before housing costs (BHC). Child poverty counts children under 16. Food bank data covers Trussell Trust network only \u2014 total food bank usage is estimated to be approximately 30% higher including independent food banks. Financial years are labelled by the end year (FYE 2023 = April 2022 to March 2023).",
